Ecology:
This species is found in clear waters, over sandy to rocky substrates, with larger adults found in deeper (> 
2 m
), slow to moderate flowing areas around large boulders or holding position in the centre of stream flow (
Fig. 7
). Juveniles are more common in moderately deep and shallow runs, darting between the cover of rocks and woody debris. Some stomachs were examined, and the contents indicated an omnivorous diet consisting mainly of insect larvae, terrestrial insects and crustaceans.
